# Copilot Documentation Rules
# This file defines where AI-generated documentation should be placed

# Rule 1: All AI analysis goes to docs/copilot/
COPILOT_DOCS_ROOT="docs/copilot"

# Rule 2: Subdirectory mapping
# analysis/ - Deep dive analysis, gap analysis, forensic reviews
# tasks/ - Task lists, quick references, action items
# plans/ - Cleanup plans, execution guides, step-by-step
# reviews/ - Implementation reviews, code reviews
# archive/ - Completed/historical documents

# Rule 3: Naming convention
# Use kebab-case: gaps-and-redundancies.md
# Include dates for time-series: review-2025-10-05.md
# Be descriptive: complete-task-list.md not tasks.md

# Rule 4: Update index
# Always update docs/copilot/README.md when adding new docs

# Rule 5: Archive old docs
# Move completed work to docs/copilot/archive/YYYY-MM/
